17. The objections againſt theſe Poſitions
are Theologicall, & not hard in Theology;
& therefore, are to be referr'd thither.

4. The firſt ſtroak produces Knowledge;
the later, actuall Memory; which,
if it be made by deſign, is call'd Remembrance.

11. And, becauſe we diſcover Suns among
thoſe other parts of the world;
'tis very credible there are proportionable
Planets diſpos'd among them, too;
and that all thoſe Bodies are mov'd in the
manner of ours.

3. Whence, tis inferr'd, that Subſtance,
as tis condiſtinct from Quantity, is indiviſible;
ſince Quantity is diviſibility.
